Post Holiday Winter Update from a very very very rainy California. Silk Long John’s have been crucial for staying warm in the garage. Dyer’s Lint is beautiful. As are accidental moons on the garage floor. And the colorful melt of ice dye. The heat of the wood fire after being outside for hours. The return of the moss and lichen. And my dog. Our walks in the rainy woods.
And honestly, I’m making an effort to really count my blessings bc these days are dark and money is tight but at least my son and I have a roof over our heads. Many don’t have that.💔

Last year this time I was in Ventura, trying to start a new life. 
Last year my ass got handed to me lol. 
I was wrong about so many things. I acted impulsively as is often my nature, and in the end, I came full circle. 
So here I am, admiring lint…it’s ok. It’s the nature of things. I saw my parents lose everything several times and rebuild again and again. I like to try to control things, outcomes, but on a spiritual level I know that’s a joke and I am ok with that, ultimately. 

C’est la vie!! 🌱🥀♥️🌱🥀

(Yes, I’m working on your orders, thank you very much for them, between the holidays, sickness and winter, things are slower but THEY ARE COMING SOON do not worry ❤️🚀🧨)

Hi!🥰
I just added these wraps (shown in Moss) to the site- I love sharing what’s working for me with you all- self care is everything!!🌹 
As I heal my curly hair after years of blow outs, and my curls return (I thought my hair had straightened with age, when really it was just needing tlc), I’m really enjoying putting them up into a silk wrap at night so that they’re fresh in the morning, without frizz✨ 
I flip my head upside down, use a silk scrunchie to loosely center it on my crown (I’ve heard this called a pineapple online 🤣)-then the wrap goes on super easily without stray hairs slipping out. I love washing my face once it’s all contained, and then when I put my eye mask on, it doesn’t smush my hair down and destroy all root volume overnight. And they serve to hold each other in place on the silk pillowcase~ perk!✨
And sometimes, yes, I leave the house in it- like here, last night, when I slipped out to pick up my son and it was snowing sideways, the wind blowing so strong- the wrap served as a comfort and made it all that much easier to warm up under the covers when back home again ❄️ and it definitely beats a shower cap! I hope you all enjoy!
 Xo🌿

There’s such a moveable line, a nebulous boundary, around sharing too much on here and no, I’m not talking about skin, although that too. I mean the inner world. I used to reveal more. Then I had too much going on to process at times much less broadcast although getting some of it out on here can help especially when I’ve isolated so thoroughly my closest friends aren’t sure where to find me.
Somewhere in Covid, in moving away, in moving back, in thriving and failing, it began to feel like nobody understood and then that left me feeling more alone and also I just assume everybody gets sick of my shit the same way I do or that it’s reduced to entertainment and while I’m happy to inspire certain emotions, scorn isn’t one of them, so I’ve pulled back and mostly just share what I make.
Over time here I’ve become fairly isolated as a single mom with chronic and invisible illness living in a small town in which I did not grow up with no family other than my son. There’s the lie that no one gets me. Heck, I don’t even get me, so who cares if no one else does either, as alluring as that sounds- to be GOT- it’s not really why we’re here, I don’t think. It’s all/we’re all changing too rapidly to achieve a fixed state of understanding anyway. So maybe there’s just awe and appreciation left- it tastes better than scorn and judgement and can be applied to everything from the trill of a bird to the light on a dumpster. Both of which are us, of course. So anyway I’m selling things and trying afford modern life in California and while I still don’t have health care at least I’ve found a variety of health practitioners willing to trade with me and I can work from home and take care of my boy when he’s sick (currently out with mono) and hang out with my dog and talk to friends all over through this evil rectangle, including you all, who still for some reason follow me despite all the complaining and thirst traps (although I have 94% female following so it’s a pretty safe space- aside from all the phishing and hacking that is lol)

Hey folks 🌸
I wanted to check in as I’m getting a lot of ‘where’s my order’ emails right now🙏 first off, thank you very much for your orders🥰The recent sales did well and as a result, I’ve been very busy. I promise you- I’m getting through them as fast as I can. There are always unseen and unexpected delays in every venture , but these are very felt by small businesses. My son was sick 2 weeks ago, with fever and all the head and tummy maladies, and things slowed down. Then I caught it and things slowed down further.m:/
I’ve been working through the holiday weekend to catch-up and I’m almost there. Many of your orders are shipping this week🙏 to those of you waiting patiently, thank you so much. I like to order things online very much as well! I love opening packages when they come in the mail. And many things I order get there the same week, next week, and I love that. But because these items are made to order, they take longer. Because they are small batch and all dyed by me, they take longer. So if you threaten to cancel your order- I really feel it. It might mean it’s hard to get groceries that week- because yes, it’s been like that. I’ve updated the turn around times online but please know it’s just a projection- if all goes well. If there’s illness or supply chain issues or shipping problems, it could be longer. Maybe this makes you not want to order. I hope not, that is not my intention- I just want to paint a more accurate picture of what it’s like fulfilling your orders…to give you more information, and maybe appeal to the kindness in your heart that you may know I am not a corporation, I feel every loss. Some days I think I’d better quit all this together and find something easier. Something where I can be in heat in the winter and air conditioning in the summer. But I am grateful I get to work with plants and color- and right now the weather is perfect and it’s a joy to be outside in it! I do not know how much longer I will do this work this way. So if you get something by me now, treasure it😌 know that it’s going to be BETTER if it’s not rushed. And thank you for reading this, if you’ve made it this far😅♥️♥️♥️ MUCH LOVE ♥️♥️♥️

Exerts from The Ponds by Mary Oliver 

Every year
the lilies
are so perfect
I can hardly believe

their lapped light crowding
the black,
mid-summer ponds.
Nobody could count all of them --

But what in this world
is perfect?

I bend closer and see
how this one is clearly lopsided --
and that one wears an orange blight --
and this one is a glossy cheek

half nibbled away --
and that one is a slumped purse
full of its own
unstoppable decay.

Still, what I want in my life
is to be willing
to be dazzled --
to cast aside the weight of facts

and maybe even
to float a little
above this difficult world.
I want to believe I am looking

into the white fire of a great mystery.
I want to believe that the imperfections are nothing --
that the light is everything -- that it is more than the sum
of each flawed blossom rising and fading. And I do.

✨✨*I do too*✨✨

I could stare at this Indigo all day🦋

My humble studio- I love all the wood and tall ceilings, and the cinder block wall behind the bank of stoves makes me feel safe.
 Yes, I have a set of gloves for every color! 🌈🧤
(Despite that, sometimes you will see spots of other colors that make it onto your item, think of them as kisses 😘)
I used to NOT wear gloves, but that was just in the beginning. I think it was good to absorb the medicine of the plant transdermaly initially, but the cracked cuticles are too painful over the long haul😮‍💨 I paint my nails to protect them from being in caustic water, that is intensely hot and cold, and currently air that is freezing. And ok, I love changing the colors twice a week;) I mostly wear black, comfy baggy layers, because ironically stains bother me when indelibrate. Dankso clogs are a must on the cement floors.
I put my favorite cream in my stories- it’s made for the face but my hands just soak it up and it heals them on the daily🙌

A Benediction for the New Year🕊️

May your heart be as soft as rain on the hungry soil. May your heart be hungry soil. May the next year be today. And every day a kingdom. May your day be filled with presence.

May presence bloom with such intensity that you stand transfixed. May there be snowdrops and trillium and columbine hung like lace across the limestone of your closed eyes. May your eyes open inwards. Downwards. Heart-towards.

May your day be as purple as your own song. As blue as your own thought. As red as the string of love you are following, step by step, through the spiral.

May you trust the seashell curvature of your becoming. May you feel yourself becoming the shape and flower of your own belonging in this one breath. This welcome, spacious hour.

by Sophie Strand @cosmogyny 💛
